race.comment: ADKI (1) has been about the money without winning, the latest offering a close fifth over 1200m at Murtoa. Has the early speed to cross from out wide. Sure to be in the finish. YONGTAI (5) hasn't won for a long time but has hit the line firmly in both runs back. Something of a trap due to her low percentage get back racing style however feel like the longer trip suits and there looks to be some speed on up front. Will take some stopping if close enough when straightening. KEITH (13) dropped out quickly when resuming off 312 days at Wagga. May need another run but is worth keeping safe on best figures. MONAGHAN'S BOY (7) has been sound enough this campaign. Keep safe.
